about.description: Arbitrary python commands for notebooks in JupyterLab
about.summary: Arbitrary python commands for notebooks in JupyterLab

name: jupyterlab_commands
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyterlab_commands" %}
{% set version = "0.2.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 54df8f23500de5bcd6fc0dab50451450fe35440ddb82aa7c3a5f9c4146bccff0

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
    - nodejs
    - jupyter-packaging
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - jupyterlab >=1.0.0
    - notebook >=6.0.3

test:
  imports:
    - jupyterlab_commands

about:
  home: http://github.com/timkpaine/jupyterlab_commands
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Arbitrary python commands for notebooks in JupyterLab

  description: |
    Arbitrary python commands for notebooks in JupyterLab
  dev_url: https://github.com/timkpaine/jupyterlab_commands

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - timkpaine
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
